section.section:
A member may not take any of the following actions without the unanimous consent of the members:
Institute a voluntary proceeding under the federal bankruptcy code;
Assign the property of the limited liability company in trust for creditors or on the assignee's promise to pay the debts of the limited liability company;
Alter the allocation of profit or loss to members of the limited liability company;
Alter the allocation of or the manner of computing distributions payable to members of the limited liability company; or
Do any other act that would make it impossible to carry on the ordinary business of the limited liability company.
